# cursorProxy Core Context

- `cursorProxy` is an edge-compatible multi-provider AI proxy for DeepSeek, Kimi, MiniMax, and Azure Foundry.
- `api/proxy.js` is the main entrypoint and holds the provider orchestration.
- `api/models.js` handles model parsing, public/private model IDs, and provider routing.
- Azure adapters live in `api/azure-openai.js` and `api/azure-anthropic.js`.
- Reasoning and cache helpers live in `api/reasoning.js`, `api/cache.js`, and `api/kv.js`.
- All `api/*.js` files are shared edge-safe modules. Do not introduce `node:*` imports or `ioredis` there.
- `server.js` is the Docker-only wrapper around the shared proxy logic.
- `vercel.json` and `edge-functions/` provide platform routing entrypoints.
- Manual verification prompts live under `.cursor/test-cases/`.
- `wiki/` is a separate git clone for the GitHub wiki. Do not commit wiki changes in the main repo.
